result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis David Obrien was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Travis David Obrien is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Travis David Obrien was found guilty of Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:02 am - DA calls case and states appearances and agreeement.  Defendant Travis David Obrien appeared in court. Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA consults with DE.  DA states facts of open Rusk County cases.  Court questions DE regarding right to attorney.  DE waives right to attorney.  DE enters plea of NO CONTEST to Ct 1 as a 1st offense.  Court questions DE regarding the plea.  DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC on Ct 1 and on motion of DA, dismissses Ct 2.  DE to submit DNA sample to PRSO.  Court imposes:

$650 fine which includes $200 DNAAS.  Pay plan of $30 per month beginning 12/31/16 and each month thereafter or CO.  Cash bond to be applied.

Appeal rights given.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 21, 2016 at 10:00 am.

If not already completed DE must submit to booking at Sheriff's Dept prior to release.
Defendant shall give written notice prior to any change in address or telephone number to the Clerk of this Court and Defense Attorney.  DE not operate a motor vehicle unless he/she has a valid dl in their possession.
